## YAML Workflow

Define blueprints as YAML files for version control and GitOps workflows:

```yaml
# blueprint.yaml
apiVersion: lyzr.ai/v1
kind: Blueprint

metadata:
  name: Customer Support
  description: Multi-agent customer support team
  category: customer
  tags: [support, automation]

spec:
  manager: agents/support-manager.yaml
  workers:
    - agents/technical-support.yaml
    - agents/billing-support.yaml
```

```yaml
# agents/support-manager.yaml
apiVersion: lyzr.ai/v1
kind: Agent

metadata:
  name: Support Manager
  description: Routes customer requests

spec:
  model: gpt-4o
  temperature: 0.3
  instructions: |
    You route customer requests to specialized agents...
```

### YAML Operations

```python
from pathlib import Path

# Create from YAML
blueprint = client.create_from_yaml(Path("my-blueprint/blueprint.yaml"))

# Update from YAML (must have IDs)
blueprint = client.update_from_yaml(Path("my-blueprint/blueprint.yaml"))

# Export to YAML
path = client.export_to_yaml(blueprint_id, Path("./exported"))

# Validate YAML without API calls
report = client.validate_yaml(Path("my-blueprint/blueprint.yaml"))
```

### CLI Commands

```bash
# Validate YAML
bp validate my-blueprint/blueprint.yaml

# Create from YAML
bp create my-blueprint/blueprint.yaml

# Update from YAML
bp update my-blueprint/blueprint.yaml

# Export to YAML
bp export <blueprint-id> -o ./exported
```

---

## API Quirks Handled

The SDK automatically handles these Lyzr API quirks:

| Quirk | Problem | SDK Solution |
|-------|---------|--------------|
| **Quadruple Storage** | Agent data stored in 4 places | Keeps all in sync |
| **managed_agents** | API-only field, not in responses | Preserved during updates |
| **NoneType Fields** | 23 fields must be arrays, never None | Auto-sanitization |
| **ReactFlow Fields** | Nodes need label, template_type | Auto-populated |

---

## Exceptions

```python
from sdk.exceptions import (
    BlueprintSDKError,      # Base exception
    APIError,               # HTTP failures
    ValidationError,        # Config validation
    AgentCreationError,     # Agent creation failed
    BlueprintCreationError, # Blueprint creation failed
    SyncError,              # Sync failures
)
```

